/var/spool/cron/crontabs	--> where crons are located
/etc/crontab	--> systemwide crontab program
/var/spool/cron	--> where users cron usually located
crontab -l	--> display current user's crontab
/var/log/syslog --> ubuntu cron log file
crontab -e	--> edit current user' crontab
crontab -e  -u user	--> root can also edit/remove any user's crontab  


0 6  * * 0 /root/backup.sh	--> run every sunday 6am
***** /root/backup.sh --> run every min
0 4,6,10 * * * --> run at 4,6,10 am
0 9-17 * * 1-5 script --> run between 9am-5pm  mon-fri
10 4,21 */3 * * script  --> run at 4:10 & 9:10pm every 3 days
@yearly script --> run every year
@monthly --> once a month at midnight first day of the month
@daily
@hourly
@reboot

